{"id": "19890", "post": "<div class=\"post-19890 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-virtual-servers category-tutorials tag-apache tag-authority tag-ca tag-certificate tag-certificate-authority tag-csr tag-encrypt tag-https tag-lets-encrypt tag-lets tag-private-key tag-public-key tag-ssl tag-ubuntu tag-virtual-private-network tag-vpn tag-web-server\" id=\"post-19890\"><h2 class=\"storytitle\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/how-to-secure-apache-with-lets-encrypt-ubuntu-16-04/\" rel=\"bookmark\">How to Secure Apache with Let\u2019s Encrypt Ubuntu 16.04</a></h2><div class=\"meta\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAMPDwwAAACwAAAAAAQABAAACAkQBADs=\" data-src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" alt=\"Tags: \"> <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/apache/\" rel=\"tag\">apache</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/authority/\" rel=\"tag\">Authority</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/ca/\" rel=\"tag\">ca</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/certificate/\" rel=\"tag\">Certificate</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/certificate-authority/\" rel=\"tag\">Certificate Authority</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/csr/\" rel=\"tag\">CSR</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/encrypt/\" rel=\"tag\">Encrypt</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/https/\" rel=\"tag\">HTTPS</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/lets-encrypt/\" rel=\"tag\">Let's Encrypt</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/lets/\" rel=\"tag\">Let\u2019s</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/private-key/\" rel=\"tag\">private key</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/public-key/\" rel=\"tag\">Public Key</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/ssl/\" rel=\"tag\">ssl</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/ubuntu/\" rel=\"tag\">ubuntu</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/virtual-private-network/\" rel=\"tag\">virtual private network</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/vpn/\" rel=\"tag\">vpn</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/web-server/\" rel=\"tag\">web server</a> <img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAMPDwwAAACwAAAAAAQABAAACAkQBADs=\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" alt=\"Date/Time: \"> June 12, 2019 @ 6:25 am, by Frank Williams</div><div class=\"storycontent tablelook\"><p>&nbsp;</p><p>In this tutorial, we will examine how to secure Apache with Let\u2019s Encrypt for the Ubuntu 16.04 operating system.&nbsp; &nbsp;We will first examine an overview of Let\u2019s Encrypt, certificate authorities, and then dive into a step by step guide to install &amp; configure Let\u2019s Encrypt on your&nbsp;Ubuntu 16.04 VPS servers and the review how to automatically renew SSL certificates.</p><p><span id=\"more-19890\"></span></p><h1><strong>What is Let\u2019s Encrypt?</strong></h1><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><strong>Let\u2019s Encrypt</strong>&nbsp;is a free, automated, and open Certificate Authority (CA), that provides the ability to secure a website. Let\u2019s Encrypt also provides automation and tools to reduce setup and maintenance challenges needed to secure web servers using HTTPS (SSL/TLS).</p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><h1><strong>Why use Let\u2019s Encrypt as your Certificate Authority?</strong></h1><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">Let\u2019s Encrypt is free, easy to create, configure, and renew certificates on web servers (like Apache).</p><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">Most administrators who host web servers have a goal of attracting new visitors along with retaining end-user attention \u2013 as this often translates into profits or a growing website community. People hosting web servers also want to reduce maintenance and cost.</p><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">End users, on the other hand, are motivated to visit websites that are safe and do not compromise their security.</p><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">To satisfy both administrators and end users, a Certificate Authority is used to validate the authenticity of the web server\u2019s domain name.</p><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">Traditional CA (Certificate Authorities) solutions like Verisign required domain owners to pay a fee to use the CA services, this is no longer required when using Let\u2019s Encrypt. The Let\u2019s encrypt service is funded by sponsors and donors.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><h1><strong>How Certificate Authority works</strong></h1><ol><li>The web server admin creates a private and public key pair. Using the public key the website admin will create a CSR (certificate signing request) and then send the CSR to a Certificate Authority.</li><li>The Certificate Authority signs the CSR and returns a final certificate that the web server admin will install on their web server.</li><li>The final certificate is signed by the Certificate Authorities private key and holds metadata about the admin\u2019s web server.</li><li>When a website visitor goes to the web page, the visitor\u2019s browser will download the final certificate from the web server. The visitor\u2019s browser will contact the Certificate Authority to make sure that the certificate downloaded from the website is valid.</li><li>If the Certificate authority confirms that the certificate is authentic/valid, the website visitor will receive a green padlock in their browser in the URL address box. This will notify the end user that the website is safe to visit.</li></ol><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><h1><strong>Prerequisites to installing Let\u2019s Encrypt on Ubuntu</strong></h1><ol><li>You must be an administrator of the domain name you want to secure; for this tutorial, we will be using the DNS hostname \u201cLetsEncryptTutorial.ddns.net.</li><li>You need to have your public IP address.</li><li>You must install Apache web server if it\u2019s not already installed.</li></ol><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI3MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMjMwIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNzAwIDIzMCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-19965\" data-src=\"http://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/binary-1538721_700_EEE.jpg.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"230\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/binary-1538721_700_EEE.jpg.webp 700w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/binary-1538721_700_EEE-300x99.jpg 300w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"></p><hr><h1><strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>Install Apache</strong></h1><ol><li>Update the Ubuntu apt repository package definitions. Open a command line terminal and type \u201capt-update\u201d or if you are logged in as a non-root user, type \u201csudo apt update\u201d.</li></ol><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI3MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMTQ3IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNzAwIDE0NyI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-19892\" data-src=\"http://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture1.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"147\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture1.png.webp 974w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture1-300x63.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture1-768x161.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><ol start=\"2\"><li>To Install Apache: \u201capt install apache2 -y\u201d or \u201csudo apt install apache2 -y\u201d</li></ol><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI3MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMjg0IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNzAwIDI4NCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-19894\" data-src=\"http://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture2.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"284\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture2.png.webp 974w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture2-300x122.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture2-768x311.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"></p><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><ol start=\"3\"><li>Change into the directory called /var/www/html and ensure an index.html file exists in the directory.</li></ol><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI2MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iNjQiIHZpZXdCb3g9IjAgMCA2MDAgNjQiPjxyZWN0IHdpZHRoPSIxMDAlIiBoZWlnaHQ9IjEwMCUiIGZpbGw9IiNjZmQ0ZGIiLz48L3N2Zz4=\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-19895\" data-src=\"http://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture3.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"64\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture3.png.webp 797w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture3-300x32.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture3-768x82.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><ol start=\"4\"><li><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Optional but recommended:</strong></span> Edit the default index.html title to be unique (example: Let\u2019s Encrypt tutorial website) by adding \u201cLet\u2019s Encrypt tutorial\u201d to the body. NOTE: This is simply to help you confirm the server is resolving and you are not accessing cached pages.</li></ol><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI3MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iNDIwIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNzAwIDQyMCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-19896\" data-src=\"http://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture4.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"420\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture4.png.webp 885w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture4-300x180.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture4-768x461.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><ol start=\"5\"><li>If using systemd for startup restart Apache \u201csystemctl restart apache2\u201d or \u201csudo systemctl restart apache2\u201d if using non-root user. If using init run \u201cservice apache2 restart\u201d</li></ol><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI3MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMTI2IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNzAwIDEyNiI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-19897\" data-src=\"http://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture5.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"126\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture5.png.webp 974w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture5-300x54.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture5-768x138.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><ol start=\"6\"><li>Confirm Apache is running properly on your system. If using systemd use \u201csystemctl status apache2\u201d and if using init use \u201cservice apache2 status\u201d</li></ol><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI3MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iNjgiIHZpZXdCb3g9IjAgMCA3MDAgNjgiPjxyZWN0IHdpZHRoPSIxMDAlIiBoZWlnaHQ9IjEwMCUiIGZpbGw9IiNjZmQ0ZGIiLz48L3N2Zz4=\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-19898\" data-src=\"http://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture6.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"68\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture6.png.webp 939w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture6-300x29.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture6-768x74.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><ol start=\"7\"><li>Confirm that the modified default Apache website is now available via a web browser</li></ol><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">First, confirm that port 80 is open and working by going to the following URL,<strong><br>\n</strong><strong>http://&lt; apache_server_ip&gt;:80 </strong>(you should see your edited webpage)</p><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">Next, confirm that the web server SSL port 443 is also open and working by going to the&nbsp;following,<br>\n<strong>https://&lt;apache_server_ip&gt;:443</strong></p><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">NOTE: When the server resolves in a browser using port 443 you will get a \u201cNot Encrypted\u201d or \u201cNot Secure\u201d error in the address bar. That\u2019s ok.</p><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><em><strong>Caution:</strong> Do not proceed to the following steps if you are not able to successfully reach your Apache server on both ports 80 and 443. If the server does not resolve to either port contact your network admins to ensure that both ports are configured to allow web traffic.</em></span><u></u></p><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI3MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMjc4IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNzAwIDI3OCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-19900\" data-src=\"http://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture8a.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"278\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture8a.png.webp 839w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture8a-300x119.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture8a-768x305.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI3MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMjc4IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNzAwIDI3OCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-19901\" data-src=\"http://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture8b.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"278\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture8b.png.webp 839w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture8b-300x119.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture8b-768x305.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong><em>Once we know Apache is resolving correctly, we can move on to the next section of this tutorial.</em></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><h1>How to set up Let\u2019s Encrypt on Apache</h1><ol><li>Install common tools \u201capt-get install software-properties-common -y\u201d if logged in as root user</li></ol><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI3MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMjQ5IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNzAwIDI0OSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-19903\" data-src=\"http://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture901.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"249\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture901.png.webp 974w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture901-300x107.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture901-768x274.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><ol start=\"2\"><li>Add the apt component for installing new repositories, by running: \u201cadd-apt-repository universe\u201d</li></ol><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI3MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMzkiIHZpZXdCb3g9IjAgMCA3MDAgMzkiPjxyZWN0IHdpZHRoPSIxMDAlIiBoZWlnaHQ9IjEwMCUiIGZpbGw9IiNjZmQ0ZGIiLz48L3N2Zz4=\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-19904\" data-src=\"http://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture902.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"39\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture902.png.webp 974w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture902-300x17.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture902-768x43.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><ol start=\"3\"><li>Add certbot to the list of apt repositories \u201cadd-apt-repository ppa:certbot/certbot\u201d</li></ol><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI3MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMjYyIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNzAwIDI2MiI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-19905\" data-src=\"http://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture903.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"262\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture903.png.webp 974w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture903-300x112.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture903-768x287.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><ol start=\"4\"><li>Update apt to detect the newly added repositories: \u201capt update\u201d</li></ol><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI3MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMjQxIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNzAwIDI0MSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-19906\" data-src=\"http://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture904.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"241\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture904.png.webp 974w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture904-300x103.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture904-768x264.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><ol start=\"5\"><li>Install certbot to create and renew certificates using let\u2019s encrypt: \u201capt-get install certbot python-certbot-apache -y\u201d</li></ol><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI3MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMTMyIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNzAwIDEzMiI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-19907\" data-src=\"http://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture905.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"132\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture905.png.webp 974w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture905-300x56.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture905-768x144.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><ol start=\"6\"><li>Run the certbot command to create SSL for your domain.</li></ol><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI3MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iODIiIHZpZXdCb3g9IjAgMCA3MDAgODIiPjxyZWN0IHdpZHRoPSIxMDAlIiBoZWlnaHQ9IjEwMCUiIGZpbGw9IiNjZmQ0ZGIiLz48L3N2Zz4=\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-19908\" data-src=\"http://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture906.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"82\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture906.png.webp 974w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture906-300x35.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture906-768x90.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI3MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMzY1IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNzAwIDM2NSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-19909\" data-src=\"http://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture906b.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"365\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture906b.png.webp 974w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture906b-300x156.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture906b-768x401.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><ol start=\"7\"><li>Now visit https://&lt;domain_name&gt; to verify that your new certificate works properly and your website has a valid certificate. You will notice a green lock icon confirming a secured connection is established with your Apache server. Click the green lock to get details about the SSL certificate.</li></ol><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI3MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMjc4IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNzAwIDI3OCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-19910\" data-src=\"http://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture907.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"278\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture907.png.webp 839w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture907-300x119.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture907-768x305.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><h1>How to automate the renewal of Let\u2019s Encrypt</h1><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">It is highly recommended to automate the renewal of your certificate to avoid http traffic interruption due to an expired SSL certificate. For Example; on the Apache server you can create a cron job to renew the certificate every month on the 10th at 6:04 am using cron by typing \u201csudo crontab -e\u201d and at the bottom add the following line (below) and save/exit.</p><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">4 6 10 * * certbot \u2013apache \u2013force-renewal renew \u2013quiet</p><p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI3MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMzkyIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNzAwIDM5MiI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-19911\" data-src=\"http://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture909.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"392\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture909.png.webp 974w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture909-300x168.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Picture909-768x430.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 700p